==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[hearm]]''

===Noun===
'''harm'''

#Injury; hurt; damage; detriment; misfortune.
#That which causes injury, damage, or loss.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[vahinko]] (1,2), [[haitta]] (2)
*Russian: [[вред]] {{m}} (vred); ущерб {{m}} [uššérp]
*Telugu: [[హాని]] (haani) (1)

===Verb===
'''harm''' ([[harms]], [[harmed]], [[harming]])

#to cause injury to another; to hurt
#To cause damage to something

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[vahingoittaa]] (1,2)
*French: [[nuire]] [[à]]
*German: [[Schaden]]

